HEADWORD: Hawkweed
<hw>Hawk"weed`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦emac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A plant of the genus
<gen>Hieracium</gen>; -- so called from the ancient belief that birds of
prey used its juice to strengthen their vision.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A plant of the genus <gen>Senecio</gen> (<spn>Senecio
hieracifolius</spn>).</def> <rj><au>Loudon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

